						<div class="postbody">ugh, I thought the data was converted from BRR to 16-bit data. now it's 15?? WTF. Even the official manual says 16-bits, but we all know it's probably crap. <br /><br />I'm so confused. My experience thus far is from converting a 16-bit PCM samples to BRR format successfully with no filter, (filter 0). That worked without any 15-bit treatment. How does that change with filters, and why did I not need to do these weird bounds checking in my filter 0 encoder?</div>

